SUBENT        C3091003   20251211   20260312   20260312       C253
BIB                  6         17
REACTION   (22-TI-0(D,X)21-SC-44-M,,SIG)
DETECTOR   (GE)
METHOD     (STTA) Three separate irradiations were performed
           with incident deuteron energies of 8.00, 7.00, and
           4.75 MeV, respectively. Approximately one day
           following the end of bombardment (allowing the foils
           to cool down), the activities were determined by
           gamma-ray spectroscopy (Canberra Coaxial P Type
           Germanium Detector).
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) The cross-section uncertainty as
           determined by gamma-ray spectroscopy is estimated by
           propagation from the error associated with counting
           statistics (A), the areal density (rho) of the
           titanium foil, and the beam current (I).
